# üöÄ feature request

### Relevant Package

- @angular/core


### Description

I would like to combine multiple input properties together. When a component has a lot of input properties and you want to pass all of them to child components, you need to manually add them where ever components need them and need to remember where you're passing them if you want to add new props.

I have a Card component which receives a lot of input properties and I do not want to use a single config property (which sure would solve this issue) for readability in this case:

```html
<app-card
        [id]="item.id"
        [type]="item.type"
        [theme]="item.theme"
        [image]="item.image"
        [title]="item.title"
        [description]="item.description"
        [timeline]="item.timeline"
        [location]="item.location"
        [categories]="item.categories"
        [collection]="item.collection"
        [joined]="item.joined"
      ></app-card>
```

Internally I use a directive that creates the correct child component for me based on the type and theme prop. Currently, I need to pass all the above props the same way down to the child component. When I now want to add a new prop it needs to be added in four places: card component* (`<app-card>`), card directive (2 times), the interface and actual card component* (based on type and theme prop).

*where I also need to specify the type again

```ts
import { Component, Input, OnInit } from '@angular/core'

@Component({
  selector: 'app-card',
  templateUrl: './card.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./card.component.scss'],
})
export class CardComponent implements OnInit {
  @Input('id') id: any // not the real type, just demo here
  @Input('type') type: any
  @Input('theme') theme: any
  @Input('image') image: any
  @Input('title') title: any
  @Input('description') description: any
  @Input('timeline') timeline: any
  @Input('location') location: any
  @Input('categories') categories: any
  @Input('collection') collection: any
  @Input('joined') joined: any

  ngOnInit() {
  }
}
```

```html
<ng-container 
[id]="id"
[type]="type"
[theme]="theme"
[image]="image"
[title]="title"
[description]="description"
[timeline]="timeline"
